volclava (2.2-0.b.20260630) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * support offloading client query requests to a dedicated query mbd subprocess with multi-threaded handling, improving query throughput and latency under high load;
  * migrate inter-process communication to epoll I/O model, enabling larger host MXJ and MAX_SBD_CONNS for large-scale clusters;
  * support LSF_NON_PRIVILEGED_PORTS to use non-privileged ports above 1024, resolving port exhaustion and connect latency under high concurrency;
  * optimize bsub -pack to batch-submit validated jobs in a single request, with LSB_PACK_SKIP_ERROR and LSB_MAX_PACK_JOBS for finer control;
  * unify merging rules for job-level and queue-level resource requirements (select/order/span/rusage) and refine bjobs -l Combined/Effective output;
  * support computing and displaying job maxMem and avgMem in bjobs -l/UF;
  * support LSB_ESUB_METHOD in lsf.conf and bsub -a/bmod -a for flexible esub configuration;
  * support bsub -Jd to attach a job description (up to 4095 chars) at submission, modifiable via bmod -Jd/-Jdn and visible in bjobs -l/bhist;
  * fix to optimize mbd-lim communication to reduce frequent calls during job dispatching;
  * fix bsub/bjobs coredump when job array is in wrong format;
  * fix host remaining in 'close' state after mbd restart if previously used by an exclusive job;
  * fix memory leak in sbatchd when starting jobs;
  * fix shell syntax in volclava.sh to support dash;

 -- Nan Qi <qinan.cn@bytedance.com>  Mon, 30 Jun 2026 18:00:00 +0800

